# 2. NEW GOVERNORS\
\
## 2.1 Governor 1: In-Chapter Explanation Cap\
\
### Rule\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f12 \cf0 Per insight, per chapter:\
  EXPLAIN beats allowed: 1\
  Additional EXPLAIN beats: FAIL (strict) or auto-downgrade to REFERENCE (lenient)
\f0 \
\
### Rationale\
\
An insight should be **explained once**. Any restatement within the same chapter is redundancy, not reinforcement.\
\
### Implementation\
\

\f12 python\
# In exhaustion_validator.py\
\
class ExhaustionValidator:\
    def __init__(self, ...):\
        # ...existing code...\
        self.explain_counts: Dict[str, Dict[int, int]] = \{\}  # insight_id -> \{chapter: count\}\
    \
    def _validate_beat(self, beat: Beat, insight_id: str) -> ValidationResult:\
        # ...existing code...\
        \
        if role == InsightRole.EXPLAIN:\
            # Check in-chapter cap\
            chapter_counts = self.explain_counts.setdefault(insight_id, \{\})\
            current_count = chapter_counts.get(beat.chapter, 0)\
            \
            if current_count >= 1:\
                return ValidationResult(\
                    beat=beat,\
                    insight_id=insight_id,\
                    status="FAIL",\
                    message=f"EXPLAIN cap exceeded: '\{insight_id\}' already explained in Ch\{beat.chapter\}",\
                    insight_state=state\
                )\
            \
            # Increment count\
            chapter_counts[beat.chapter] = current_count + 1\
            \
            # ...rest of existing EXPLAIN logic...
